<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/2943635-nea"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1531892069i/2943635._UX100_CR0,3,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2943635-nea">Nea</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Polly Shine helped to make sure the baby wasn't born alive. There was a large clay urn in the corner with a bloody rag laying across it and Polly jerk<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Polly Shine helped to make sure the baby wasn't born alive. There was a large clay urn in the corner with a bloody rag laying across it and Polly jerked Granada back so she couldn't look in it. This is why Granada reported that they killed the baby. When Granada confronts Polly about killing "one of 'the people,'" Polly explains that "the people" is about more than their flesh and blood. It also means their voices. The power to say yes or no. She explains that the incident (killing the baby) was Rubina's way using her voice. She made a decision for herself and her child. With Polly's help, Rubina took away the white man's power to control her yes's and no's. <br /><br />"Rubina said no. In ever which away she could, she say no! With all her woman's voice. She weren't lukewarm about it. As much as a person could, she said no. That's got to count for something." <br /><br />I hope this helps.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
