<div id="review_396997350" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/396997350" />
    <a title="Tara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1663300-tara"><img alt="Tara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1508879587p2/1663300.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/396997350?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tara" href="/user/show/1663300-tara">Tara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780307744562" href="/book/show/13536265-the-healing">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer396997350" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18206807643897440546">A great deal of research went into this book, and it shows, without being glaringly educational. An intense look at plantation life from the pov of the &quot;swamp slave,&quot; and a respectful exploration of the role midwives played amongst the slave population before the 1950s. A very female-centered book, this story highlights the importance of oral history and has one of the best definitions of freedom I&apos;ve ever heard:<br/><br/>&quot;All Freedom is two words: &apos;Yes&apos; and &apos;No.&apos;&quot;<br/><br/>So simple, but so true, this book delves </span>
  <span id="freeText18206807643897440546" style="display:none">A great deal of research went into this book, and it shows, without being glaringly educational. An intense look at plantation life from the pov of the "swamp slave," and a respectful exploration of the role midwives played amongst the slave population before the 1950s. A very female-centered book, this story highlights the importance of oral history and has one of the best definitions of freedom I've ever heard:<br /><br />"All Freedom is two words: 'Yes' and 'No.'"<br /><br />So simple, but so true, this book delves into some dark places and the spiritual realm of those who are gifted with the "sight." Will appeal to anyone who loves historical fiction and fiction that depicts well-rounded minorities. Odell is an author I will read again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18206807643897440546" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
